{"art": [{"brightcove": "", "caption": "An Americans for Prosperity ad attacks Obama over his promise to halve the deficit.", "id": 2669, "infogram": "", "ndn": "", "ndnid": "", "other": "", "photo": null, "resource_type": {"id": 2, "name": "YouTube", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/mediatype/2/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/media/2669/", "title": "Americans for Prosperity obama debt", "wibbitz": "", "youtube": "<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/2S8rHJtLJE0?rel=0&wmode=opaque\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>", "youtubeID": "2S8rHJtLJE0"}], "author": [{"email_address": "jgillin@politifact.com", "first_name": "Joshua", "id": 327, "last_name": "Gillin", "name_slug": "joshua-gillin", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": "727-893-8337", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/joshuagillin.jpg", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/327/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "jpgillin"}], "canonical_url": "/florida/statements/2012/aug/16/americans-prosperity/obama-national-debt-held-accountable-one-term/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Florida", "edition": "Florida", "edition_slug": "florida", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 4, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Florida Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/4/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "aholan@poynter.org", "first_name": "Angie Drobnic", "id": 8, "last_name": "Holan", "name_slug": "angie-drobnic-holan", "on_staff_page": 1, "phone": "727-410-1770", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots07.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/8/", "title": "Editor", "twitter": "AngieHolan"}], "facebook_headline": null, "id": 6469, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "jgillin@politifact.com", "first_name": "Joshua", "id": 327, "last_name": "Gillin", "name_slug": "joshua-gillin", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": "727-893-8337", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/joshuagillin.jpg", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/327/", "title": "Staff Writer", "twitter": "jpgillin"}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/6469/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "False", "id": 5, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/5/", "ruling": "False", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-false.png", "ruling_slug": "false"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>\r\n\tA new commercial from the conservative group Americans for Prosperity accuses Obama of breaking his promises on the national debt.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe ad notes, &quot;In 2009, Barack Obama said,&quot; then cuts to Obama: &quot;I&rsquo;m pledging to cut the deficit by half by the end of my first term in office.&quot; The words &quot;Feb. 2009, Debt: $10 trillion&quot; flash onscreen.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tA giant meter titled &quot;the national debt clock&quot; then appears on screen, reading $10.6 trillion. As talking heads recount the upward spiral of the nation&rsquo;s debt, the clock frantically spins above $15 trillion.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tObama is then heard saying, &quot;I will be held accountable&quot; before appearing in a video and continuing, &quot;If I don&#39;t have this done in three years, then there&#39;s going to be a one-term proposition.&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe debt clock returns, reading in excess of $15.9 trillion with the tagline, &quot;Let&rsquo;s make this a one-term proposition on November 6th.&quot; In a voice-over, the president is heard repeating, &quot;I will be held accountable.&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWell, time&rsquo;s up, Mr. President. Did Obama say he would be held accountable for not halving the deficit in three years? When we went to the tape, we found Americans for Prosperity was pulling together two different interviews, and on two different topics.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<strong>The deficit debate</strong><br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tFirst off, it should be no secret Obama did, in fact, promise to cut the deficit in half during his first term. We&rsquo;ve confirmed that before, rating that very claim by Republican Party of Florida chairman Lenny Curry quite <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/florida/statements/2012/mar/08/lenny-curry/obama-promised-cut-deficit-half-end-his-first-term/\">True</a>.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThat ruling pointed out the federal budget deficit -- the difference between what the government spends versus what it takes in -- was $1.4 trillion when Obama took office. It decreased each year, projected to reach $901 billion in the fiscal year 2013 budget, but that&rsquo;s still over the promised amount, which would have been in the neighborhood of $700 billion.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWith the presence of the debt clock, Americans For Prosperity is confusing the deficit with the national debt, which is the aggregated total of the nation&rsquo;s public debt, not its annual budget deficits. AFP didn&rsquo;t return our request for clarification, so we can only guess if they know the difference. Most Americans <a href=\"http://pewresearch.org/pubs/1804/political-news-quiz-iq-deficit-defense-spending-tarp-inflation-boehner\">don&rsquo;t seem to know the specifics</a>, either.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe promise Obama made was from a White House meeting called the &quot;Fiscal Responsibility Summit&quot; on Feb. 23, 2009.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;Today I&#39;m pledging to cut the deficit we inherited by half by the end of my first term in office,&quot; Obama <a href=\"http://www.whitehouse.gov/assets/blog/Fiscal_Responsibility_Summit_Report.pdf\">said</a>. &quot;Now, this will not be easy. It will require us to make difficult decisions and face challenges we&#39;ve long neglected. But I refuse to leave our children with a debt that they cannot repay, and that means taking responsibility right now, in this administration, for getting our spending under control.&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tNote the phrase &quot;we inherited&quot; was removed from the ad&rsquo;s version. That alone doesn&rsquo;t make AFP&rsquo;s usage of the sentence for the purposes of this attack ad untrue; Despite the president&rsquo;s reasoning that high unemployment, wartime costs and the Great Recession prevented deeper cuts, budget numbers are still budget numbers.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<strong>Staying on message</strong><br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe selective editing gets worse in the second half of the ad.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tObama&rsquo;s admission that the voters will likely break out the torches and pitchforks if he doesn&rsquo;t follow through in three years is from a 2009 interview with Matt Lauer on NBC&rsquo;s <em>Today </em>show.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tIt&rsquo;s from Feb. 2, however, almost three weeks before his pledge to cut the deficit.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tAnd the president is speaking about the Troubled Asset Relief Program, not halving the deficit.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tDuring the interview, Lauer asked Obama if the bank bailouts he inherited would be curtailed if spending appeared to be ineffective. (President George W. Bush signed TARP into law October 2008, before Obama was elected.)<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;Look, I&#39;m at the start of my administration,&quot; Obama said. &quot;One nice thing about the situation I find myself in is that I will be held accountable. You know, I&#39;ve got four years, and --&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;You&#39;re going to know quickly how people feel about what&#39;s happening,&quot; Lauer interjected.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;That&#39;s exactly right. And, you know, a year from now, I think people are going to see that we&#39;re starting to make some progress, but there&#39;s still going to be some pain out there. If I don&#39;t have this done in three years, then there&#39;s going to be a one-term proposition.&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tFor the record, TARP officially expired in October 2010. The net cost of the program to U.S. taxpayers was reported earlier this year to be in the neighborhood of $34 billion, although questions remain as to exactly how some banks repaid the bulk of some $428 billion in disbursements and whether many banks in the program were going to survive. But no more money is being lent from the TARP fund.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWe should note there&rsquo;s been a troubling trend this election season of campaigns splicing together unrelated or out-of-context video of a candidate&rsquo;s statements.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tMitt Romney&rsquo;s campaign used Obama&rsquo;s &quot;you didn&rsquo;t build that&quot; quote <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2012/jul/26/mitt-romney/putting-mitt-romneys-attacks-you-didnt-build-truth/\">out of context</a>, but Democrats have also deceptively quoted Romney&rsquo;s stance on his Massachusetts <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2011/nov/29/democratic-national-committee/dnc-ad-accuses-mitt-romney-flip-flopping-assault-w/\">ban on assault weapons</a> and <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2011/nov/01/democratic-national-committee/ad-claims-mitt-romneys-housing-policy-let-foreclos/\">dealing with foreclosures</a>.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEditing video to make a person say what you want is not a new tactic, nor is it that hard to do -- here&rsquo;s a video of Obama singing <a href=\"http://youtu.be/hX1YVzdnpEc\">Carly Rae Jepsen&rsquo;s Call Me Maybe</a>.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<strong>The ruling</strong><br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tClearly this commercial is edited to remove references to the Bush administration and muddy the context of the president&rsquo;s comments. Obama irrefutably made the promise in 2009 to slash the deficit in half by the time his first term expired, and that doesn&rsquo;t look at all possible.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tBut Americans For Prosperity overreaches, splicing together footage from two unrelated interviews to distort the message it wants to convey. Obama wasn&rsquo;t talking about the deficit or the debt when he said, &quot;If I don&#39;t have this done in three years, then there&#39;s going to be a one-term proposition.&quot;<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tIn this instance, the piling on is unnecessary to make the group&rsquo;s point, and it&rsquo;s intentionally misleading. The ad takes Obama&rsquo;s comments from an interview about bank bailouts and TARP and makes it look as if he&rsquo;s talking about the national debt. The use of the debt clock also purposely detracts from the president&rsquo;s initial statement about the federal deficit.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWe rate this claim False.</p>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2012-08-14T14:53:55.867037", "ruling_date": "2012-08-16T06:00:00", "ruling_headline": "Did Obama say of the national debt, \u201cIf I don't have this done in three years, then there's going to be a one-term proposition\u201d?", "ruling_headline_slug": "obama-national-debt-held-accountable-one-term", "ruling_link_text": "Creative editing confuses the issue", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>\r\n\tYouTube, &quot;<a href=\"http://youtu.be/2S8rHJtLJE0\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \">President Obama: A One Term Proposition</a>,&quot; posted Aug. 8, 2012<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tWhite House, &quot;<a href=\"http://www.whitehouse.gov/assets/blog/Fiscal_Responsibility_Summit_Report.pdf\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \">Fiscal Responsibility Summit remarks</a>,&quot; Feb. 23, 2009<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tC-SPAN Video Library, &quot;<a href=\"http://www.c-spanvideo.org/program/284237-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \">White House Fiscal Responsibility Summit</a>,&quot; minute 24:36, Feb. 23, 2009<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tYouTube via the Today show, &quot;<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=daHXJco82fw\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \">Feb 2, Matt Lauer interview with President Barack Obama</a>,&quot; minute 4:20, Feb. 2, 2009<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tNexis&nbsp;Federal News Service transcript, &quot;NBC &lsquo;Today&rsquo; interview with President Barack Obama; Interviewer: Matt Lauer,&quot; Feb. 2, 2009<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tCongressional Budget Office, &quot;<a href=\"http://www.cbo.gov/publication/22076\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \">Report on the Troubled Asset Relief Program</a>,&quot; March 29, 2011<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\t<br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \" />\r\n\tWhite House, &quot;<a href=\"http://www.whitehouse.gov/omb/budget/Overview/\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transf